    "body": "# cudaMemcpy may hurt performace in gemm grouped\r\nWe use cutlass 2.x api to launch a grouped gemm in some gpus which cc < 90. We find that if we use kHostPrecompute as GroupScheduleMode, cutlass will compute some schedule meta info on host, and then copy it to GPU by a cudaMemcpy api with default stream and sync semantic: https://github.com/NVIDIA/cutlass/blob/81a43e6d92cdd8c20d22392f9579604ed5f710a1/include/cutlass/gemm/device/base_grouped.h#L131\r\n\r\nThis may hurt performance. So we use cudaMemcpyAsync in grouped gemm.",
    "created_at": "2025-04-21T08:05:55Z",
